item.description:
Calling TCL from C Starting with working example, we can see that Tcl_CreateInterp and Tcl_Eval are the only two Tcl calls.
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;#include &lt;tcl.h&gt; main (int argc, char *argv[]) { Tcl_Interp *myinterp; char *action = &#34;set a [expr 5 * 8]; puts $a&#34;; int status; printf (&#34;Your Program will run ... \n&#34;); myinterp = Tcl_CreateInterp(); status = Tcl_Eval(myinterp,action); printf (&#34;Your Program has completed\n&#34;); } And compilation command
gcc main.c -I /usr/include/tcl8.
